'''Memo Benassi''' (21 June 1886 – 24 February 1957) was an Italian [[film actor]] who appeared in more than forty films in a mixture of [[leading role|leading]] and [[supporting role]]s. He played the composer [[Beethoven]] in the 1942 film ''[[Rossini (film)|Rossini]]''.<ref>Mathew & Walton p.337</ref>

==Selected filmography==
* ''[[The Love Letters of Baroness S]]'' (1924)
* ''[[The Adventures of Sybil Brent]]'' (1925)
* ''[[The Old Lady]]'' (1932)
* ''[[The Lucky Diamond]]'' (1933)
* ''[[The Haller Case]]'' (1933)
* ''[[Everybody's Woman]]'' (1934)
* ''[[Conquest of the Air]]'' (1936)
* ''[[Scipione l'africano]]'' (1937)
* ''[[Princess Tarakanova (1938 film)|Princess Tarakanova]]'' (1938)
* ''[[Tonight at Eleven]]'' (1938)
* ''[[The Two Orphans (1942 film)|The Two Orphans]]'' (1942)
* ''[[Rossini (film)|Rossini]]'' (1942)
* ''[[Fedora (1942 film)|Fedora]]'' (1942)
* ''[[Measure for Measure (1943 film)|Measure for Measure]]'' (1943)
* ''[[The Tyrant of Padua]]'' (1946)
* ''[[The Affairs of Messalina]]'' (1951)
* ''[[Red Shirts (film)|Red Shirts]]'' (1952)
* ''[[Adriana Lecouvreur (film)|Adriana Lecouvreur]]'' (1955)

